<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1752,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1752,1777]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Shell trigonal, ventral margin rounded to straight, posterior area delimited by a line; periostracum brownish, almost absent in the umbonal area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1752,2028]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,572]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1824,1849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Description.</emphasis>
Shell trigonal, inequilateral, strong, large (up to 
<quantity box="[897,980,1824,1848]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="65.0">65 mm</quantity>
); external surface smooth with commarginal lines close to the umbonal area; periostracum brownish and thin; anterior dorsal margin straight, posterior rounded; right hinge with two divergent cardinals (
<number box="[727,740,1896,1920]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
a &amp; 
<number box="[791,805,1896,1920]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
b), unfused; anterior lateral teeth (AI &amp; 
<collectionCode box="[1259,1312,1896,1920]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">AIII</collectionCode>
), short and close to cardinals; posterior lateral teeth present (PI &amp; 
<collectionCode box="[771,816,1932,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">PIII</collectionCode>
) (
<figureCitation box="[840,908,1932,1956]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1109,1132]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1087]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1088]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mactra fuegiensis, A – B: hinge description according to the nomenclature developed by Bernard &amp; Munier Chalmas, scale bar = 1 cm; C – D: Ultrastructure of the shell, C general aspect, ol: outer layer, il: inner layer; D: detail of the inner layer with the cross lamellar complex, scale bar = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201080/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[894,908,1932,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B). V-shaped cardinal tooth in left valve (
<number box="[1379,1393,1932,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
a &amp; 
<number box="[151,167,1968,1992]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
b). One anterior and one posterior lateral tooth (AII &amp; PII) running parallel to the dorsal shell margin; each elongated, fragile, with one cusp (
<figureCitation box="[484,549,2004,2028]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1109,1132]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1087]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1088]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mactra fuegiensis, A – B: hinge description according to the nomenclature developed by Bernard &amp; Munier Chalmas, scale bar = 1 cm; C – D: Ultrastructure of the shell, C general aspect, ol: outer layer, il: inner layer; D: detail of the inner layer with the cross lamellar complex, scale bar = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201080/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[536,549,2004,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A); external ligament rudimentary, posterior to umbos; internal ligament (resilium) large, strong, in chondrophore. Muscle scar semicircular, vertically elongated, with dorsal and ventral ends pointed, close to dorsal edge; pallial sinus rounded, 
<number box="[733,743,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[754,768,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="3.0">3</number>
of total shell length (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1098,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. A – H" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,625,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,625,1899]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A – H: Syntypes of Mactra fuegiensis Smith (NHM 1905.8.11.7 - 10); I – L: holotype of Mactra epidermia Philippi, 1893 (MNHNC), scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201079/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[1060,1075,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="2.0">2</number>
D
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Ultrastructure of the shell with two layers, outer crossed lamellar of elongated crystallites arranged into lamellae; crystallites in the adjacent lamellae differ in alignment by approximately 
<number box="[1011,1086,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="94.0" valueMax="98.0" valueMin="90.0">90–98</number>
°. Inner complex crossed lamellar, consisting of intergrowth pattern resulting from crossed lamellar structure in two alignments (
<figureCitation box="[1243,1308,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1109,1132]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1087]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1088]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mactra fuegiensis, A – B: hinge description according to the nomenclature developed by Bernard &amp; Munier Chalmas, scale bar = 1 cm; C – D: Ultrastructure of the shell, C general aspect, ol: outer layer, il: inner layer; D: detail of the inner layer with the cross lamellar complex, scale bar = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201080/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[1295,1308,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C–D). 
<emphasis box="[151,388,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Mantle cavity organs</emphasis>
: Labial palps very elongated in relation to body size (
<figureCitation box="[994,1062,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1747,1770]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1242,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1242,1726]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mactra fuegiensis, A: SEM picture of the outer labial palp (olp), external view smooth and internal view plicate, scale bar = 2 mm; B: SEM picture of the incurrent (in) and excurrent (ex) siphons, scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201081/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[1047,1062,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). External demibranch fused to mantle. Siphons completely fused, covered by periostracum (
<figureCitation box="[837,905,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1747,1770]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1242,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1242,1726]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mactra fuegiensis, A: SEM picture of the outer labial palp (olp), external view smooth and internal view plicate, scale bar = 2 mm; B: SEM picture of the incurrent (in) and excurrent (ex) siphons, scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201081/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[889,905,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
