<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[321,522,188,212]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mactridae" genus="Mactra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fuegiensis">
<emphasis box="[321,522,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Mactra fuegiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[746,787,188,212]" name="Iceland" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Isla</collectingCountry>
Grande de Tierra del Fuego coast. It is well represented in the Magellanic Province and constitutes the southernmost species of 
<taxonomicName box="[953,1035,225,248]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mactridae" genus="Mactra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[953,1035,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Mactra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from South 
<collectingCountry box="[1186,1286,223,247]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">America</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Philippi, 1893" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1893" class="Bivalvia" family="Mactridae" genus="Mactra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="epidermia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Mactra epidermia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Philippi" box="[243,407,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" refString="Philippi, R. A. (1893) Las especies chilenas del genero Mactra. Anales del Museo Nacional de Chile, Zoologia, 1 - 15." type="book chapter" year="1893">
Philippi, 
<number box="[351,407,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1893.0">1893</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(non Deshayes in 
<bibRefCitation author="Reeve" box="[639,788,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" refString="Reeve, L. (1854) Monograph of the genus Mactra. In Reeve, L. (1843.1873) Conchologia Iconica; or, Illustrations of the shells of Molluscous Animals. London, 8, 21 pls." type="journal article" year="1854">
Reeve, 
<number box="[728,788,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1854.0">1854</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), is a junior homonym (
<figureCitation box="[1084,1156,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. A – H" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,625,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,625,1899]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A – H: Syntypes of Mactra fuegiensis Smith (NHM 1905.8.11.7 - 10); I – L: holotype of Mactra epidermia Philippi, 1893 (MNHNC), scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201079/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<date box="[1142,1156,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<number box="[1142,1156,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
</date>
</figureCitation>
I–L) (
<taxonomicName authority="Deshayes" authorityName="Deshayes" class="Bivalvia" family="Mactridae" genus="Mactra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="epidermia">
<emphasis box="[1227,1436,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Mactra epidermia</emphasis>
Deshayes
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Reeve" box="[303,450,295,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" refString="Reeve, L. (1854) Monograph of the genus Mactra. In Reeve, L. (1843.1873) Conchologia Iconica; or, Illustrations of the shells of Molluscous Animals. London, 8, 21 pls." type="journal article" year="1854">
Reeve, 
<number box="[391,450,295,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1854.0">1854</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, with 
<collectingCountry box="[527,622,295,319]" name="Portugal" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Portugal</collectingCountry>
as 
<typeStatus box="[668,716,296,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">type</typeStatus>
locality, has priority over Philippi’s species). 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernard" box="[1260,1436,295,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="65" refString="Bernard, F. R. (1983) Catalogue of the living Bivalvia of the eastern Pacific Ocean: Bering Strait to Cape Horn. Canadian Special Publication of Fisheries and Aquatic Sciences, 61, 1 - 102." type="journal article" year="1983">
Bernard (
<number box="[1370,1428,295,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1983.0">1983</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
wrongly included both nominal taxa as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authority="King &amp; Broderip, 1832" authorityName="King &amp; Broderip" authorityYear="1832" box="[754,1194,332,356]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mactridae" genus="Mulinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="edulis">
<emphasis box="[754,918,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Mulinia edulis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="King" box="[926,1194,332,356]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" refString="King, P. P. &amp; Broderip, W. J. (1832) Description of the Cirripedia, Conchifera and Mollusca in a collection formed by the officers of HMS Adventure and Beagle employed between the years 1826 and 1830 in surveying the southern coasts of South America, including the straits of Magalhaens and the coast of Tierra del Fuego. Zoological Journal, 5, 332 - 349." type="journal article" year="1832">
King &amp; Broderip, 
<number box="[1135,1194,332,356]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1832.0">1832</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[1206,1409,332,356]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mactridae" genus="Mactra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fuegiensis">
<emphasis box="[1206,1409,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Mactra fuegiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a trigonal shell with a straight ventral margin and an external ligament clearly not observed in 
<taxonomicName authority="King &amp; Broderip, 1832" authorityName="King &amp; Broderip" authorityYear="1832" box="[151,584,404,428]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mactridae" genus="Mulinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="edulis">
<emphasis box="[151,313,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Mulinia edulis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="King" box="[320,584,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" refString="King, P. P. &amp; Broderip, W. J. (1832) Description of the Cirripedia, Conchifera and Mollusca in a collection formed by the officers of HMS Adventure and Beagle employed between the years 1826 and 1830 in surveying the southern coasts of South America, including the straits of Magalhaens and the coast of Tierra del Fuego. Zoological Journal, 5, 332 - 349." type="journal article" year="1832">
King &amp; Broderip, 
<number box="[526,584,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1832.0">1832</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which it otherwise closely resembles.
</paragraph>
